      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CADILLAC BELLE (5) generally breaks well and with clear running can clear the draw. Last start finished 4th on June 28 over 305m at this track behind Energy To Burn beaten 6 lengths (18.05) in a Grade 5. Rates on top and should go close. HARRY CHANA (7) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when third (17.91) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Hard to beat again. TESTED (2) turned in a plain run last time when sixth at this track over 400m behind Aston Deutz (23.67) in a Grade 6. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to her name from 10 starts. Better than last start and can bounce back. IMPRESS JOE (1) jumps at a shorter journey and still warrants respect.",
